5:
I suppose I should tell you a bit
about what happened afterwards.
30:
Oh no... No, no, no!
Gaaaah!
34:
Quit your pathetic mewling, would
you? You know very well that this
was the optimal solution.
44:
Aliksir—formerly the Guardian from
the Palace of the Stars—became our
ally. For some reason, she began
studying under Nephtim. I guess
that kind of makes sense, now that I
think about it.
47:
Aliksir is still a newbie, and lacks
"rizz." It is imperative to gain more
influence and mutual
understanding with others. Do you
understand your mission?
51:
Affirmative. However, Aliksir must
posit a query—what does your heart
seek, Sister Nephtim? What brings
you satisfaction?
57:
Nephtim's dream is to be a TOP
entertainer. Designating next goal:
1,000,000 subs.
61:
That's it! Yes, the same as the Circle
of Growth!
65:
Wait... You're talking about the
Abyss, right? Not whatever the heck
Nephtim just said?
70:
Obviously. Imagine, for a second,
the force of waves beating against
a levee. Once a crack
emerges—sooner or later—the levee
WILL break.
73:
Before that happens, a sluice gate
must be put in place, to allow the
stream to be controlled.
78:
The sleepers feared change.
Aliksir wonders if your companions
fear it as well.
84:
No. Alk and the others are not like
that.
88:
Gram, on the other hand, might not
be the biggest fan of this
suggestion...
91:
After that, the Abyss Exploration
Team was established to look for
paths to distant worlds—much to
Gram's chagrin.
96:
All right, everyone! Ready for an
adventure?!
101:
Don't get lost now! Stick with the
team!
112:
What? You have something to say?
One more word about how
"dangerous" this is and I'll shove
macaroni up your nose, Yumu.
117:
N-nope... No complaints here... But
come on, Nao. I'm your big brother.
I'm allowed to worry!
122:
We've gotta establish a connection
in exactly the right place, and Nao
here's the best gal for the job!
126:
I know, I know. I'm just nervous.
There's still a certain guy in black
robes to worry about, in case you
forgot.
132:
Him? Pfft, please! We can handle a
little weasel like him, no problem!
138:
Heh-heh. I say let him worry! We'll
see how Yumu likes the taste of his
own medicine!
141:
What was supposed to be a "short"
expedition ended up lasting an
entire anxiety-inducing month.
Apparently, they got sidetracked
saving some far-off world.
142:
To be fair, escapades like that are
just a regular day for the Crimson
Blades. Nao was right—waiting was
painful... It made me think real hard
about my own actions.
145:
Oh, and there was one more big
piece of news.
148:
Light gained the ability to turn back
into a human.
154:
Sweet jumping jackals—why the hell
are you just a kid?!
160: Light! You're so small... and soft!
165:
I... had to do a bit of improvisation.
Give us a break, we JUST got
reincarnated ourselves too!
Whatever—at least he's cute, right?
170:
The power of the Champion will
likely not return to you. What's more,
your form may revert to your
previous appearance from time to
time...
175:
It is of no consequence. I'm more
than pleased with what you've been
able to do. Thank you, both of you!
179:
Wh-what is the matter, Arum? Is
something wrong?
183:
Ehehe! You look cooler now, buuut
you still smell like Light!
187:
Oh, hey! Now that you look like this,
that means we can get married!
193:
Um. I'm not so sure that would be a
good idea.
197:
Yeah, uh, you might wanna wait a
few years for that.
203:
Of course we would wait a
few—wait, NO! I never agreed to this!
W-we are NOT getting married!
208:
All I'm saying is, you'd look extra cute
in an itty-bitty tuxedo!
214:
I-itty-bitty?! I am a FULLY GROWN
ADULT MALE, and I demand that you
treat me as such!
218:
Belsidia... Was this prank your doing?
I can't believe you'd stoop this low—
222:
O-oh my. So... darn... cute! Don't
think I'll be giving you special
treatment just because you're a
precious cutie patootie all of a
sudden!
231:
*sigh* I don't suppose you two can
try to get me back to my proper
adult form?
235: R-right... We'll do what we can!
238:
Stella laughs more these days. And
louder, too.
244:
I'm not here to be your friend or
anything.
248: Here it is, precisely as I promised!
251:
Gramp Zigza FINALLY published the
newest edition of KoiAzu—and to
think, all it took was giving him a
quick kick upside the rump!
256:
Oh, I've been waiting for this for so
long... I can't possibly thank you
enough, Inaho!
265:
Blood-red pancakes, topped with
liquid acid and tapioca "meteors."
273:
Gah, hold on, now I'm getting
distracted! There was something I
wanted to ask you.
276: Why... did you save me? Back then.
285:
I didn't want you to disappear and
merge with me.
